articles.description: Payton Pritchard had 19 points and 10 assists, and Troy Brown Jr. also had a double-double to lead Oregon past Washington State 84-57 on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Pritchard, Brown lead Oregon to 84-57 win over Washington St

articles.description: Shep Garner scored 16 points and Tony Carr had 15 points to lead Penn State to a 74-52 victory over Illinois on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Garner, Carr help Penn State beat Illinois 74-52

videos.description: Jalen Brunson gets the ball to Donte DiVincenzo down low and he elevates for the slam.
videos.headline: DiVincenzo gets easy dunk for Villanova

videos.description: Donte DiVincenzo uses a nice bounce pass to get the ball to Dhamir Cosby-Roundtree who finishes with a dunk for Villanova.
videos.headline: DiVincenzo sets up Cosby-Roundtree slam

videos.description: B.J. Johnson finishes an alley-oop with a dunk then drains a 3-pointer to give the Explorers an early lead over No. 4 Villanova.
videos.headline: Johnson's back-to-back buckets give La Salle a lead on Villanova

videos.description: Jalen Brunson pulls up but then decides to bounce it over to Mikal Bridges who gets the bucket and draws contact.
videos.headline: Villanova's Bridges makes tough layup through foul

videos.description: Tony Washinton elevates for the dunk and Phil Booth gets a block from behind to shut down the Explorers.
videos.headline: Booth rejects La Salle dunk attempt

videos.description: Isiah Deas kicks it out to B.J. Johnson who makes the three, giving him 21 points vs. Villanova.
videos.headline: Johnson drains corner 3 to close gap vs. Villanova

videos.description: Donte DiVincenzo extends Villanova's lead with a long 3-pointer.
videos.headline: DiVincenzo answers with a 3-pointer
